definition.value: An aminoheptasaccharide consisting of five hexosyl and two acetaminohexosyl groups (identities and connectivity unknown). Composition: Hex5 HexNAc2.
A partially-defined glycan consisting of unknown numbers of hexosyl and acetaminohexosyl groups (identities and connectivity unknown). Composition: Hex? HexNAc?.
A partially-defined glycan consisting of nine hexosyl and two acetaminohexosyl groups (identities and connectivity unknown). Composition: Hex9 HexNAc2.

A partially-defined glycan consisting of five hexosyl groups, four acetaminohexosyl groups, a 6-deoxyhexosyl group and an N-acetcylneuraminic acid group (identities and connectivity unknown). Composition: Hex5 HexNAc4 6dHex1 Neu5Ac1.
An amino decasaccharide consisting of five hexosyl groups, four acetaminohexosyl groups and an N-acetcylneuraminic acid group (identities and connectivity unknown). Composition: Hex5 HexNAc4 Neu5Ac1.
A partially-defined glycan consisting of three hexosyl groups, 2 acetominohexosyl groups and a 6-deoxyhexosyl group (identities and connectivity unknown). Composition: Hex3 HexNAc2 6dHex1.
An partially-defined glycan that is an acetaminohexose in which the identity of the acetaminohexose and configuration of the anomeric centre is not known.
An amino decasaccharide consisting of five hexosyl groups, four acetaminohexosyl groups and a 6-deoxyhexosyl group (identities and connectivity unknown). Composition: Hex5 HexNAc4 6-dHex1.
A glucuronosylinositol phosphorylceramide in which the acyl group is hydroxylated at position 2 and the ceramide base is hydroxylated at position 4.
An aminodecasaccharide consisting of six hexosyl groups, three acetaminohexosyl groups and an N-acetylneuaminic acid group (identities and connectivity unknown). Composition: Hex6 HexNAc3 Neu5Ac1.
An amino pentasaccharide  consisting of three hexosyl groups and two acetaminohexosyl groups (identities and connectivity unknown). Composition: Hex3 HexNAc2.
The 11-hydroperoxy derivative of linoleic acid having (S)-configuration.

An amino octasaccharide consisting of four hexosyl groups, three acetaminohexosyl groups and an N-acetcylneuraminic acid group (identities and connectivity unknown). Composition: Hex4 HexNAc3 Neu5Ac1.
The (R)-enantiomer of toloxatone.
The (S)-enantiomer of toloxatone.
A member of the class of oxazolidinones that is 5-(hydroxymethyl)-1,3-oxazolidin-2-one substituted by a 3-methylphenyl group at position 3.
A 4-[2-[[1-hydroxy-1-(4-hydroxyphenyl)propan-2-yl]amino]ethyl]phenol that has (1S,2R)-configuration.
A dihydroxy monocarboxylic acid that is the 7(S),8(S)-dihydroxy derivative of linoleic acid.

An amino decasaccharide that is alpha-D-Manp-(1->2)-alpha-D-Manp-(1->2)-alpha-D-Manp-(1->3)-[alpha-D-Manp-(1->3)-[alpha-D-Manp-(1->6)]-alpha-D-Manp-(1->6)]-beta-D-Manp-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcpNAc-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcpNAc which contains an additional D-mannospyranose unit attached by an (alpha-1->2) glycosidic bond. In the structure shown, one of the five R atoms represents the alpha-1->2 attached mannosyl group; the remaining four R atoms are hydrogens.

An amino polysaccharide that is alpha-D-Manp-(1->3)-[beta-D-Manp-(1->6)]-beta-D-Manp-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcpNAc-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcpNAc in which one hydroxy group in each of the terminal mannose moieties has been converted into the corresponding Neu5Ac-(1->?)-?-D-Gal-(1->?)-?-D-GlcNAc-(1->?)- glycoside. For the structure shown, one of the R1 atoms and one of the R2 atoms represents a Neu5Ac-(1->?)-?-D-Gal-(1->?)-?-D-GlcNAc-(1->?)- group; the remaining R1 and R2 aroms are hydrogens.

An amino nonasaccharide that is alpha-D-Manp-(1->3)-[beta-D-Manp-(1->6)]-beta-D-Manp-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcpNAc-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcpNAc in which one hydroxy group in each of the terminal mannose moieties has been converted into the corresponding D-Gal-(1->?)-?-D-GlcNAc-(1->?)- glycoside. For the structure shown, one of the R1 atoms and one of the R2 atoms represents a ?-D-Gal-(1->?)-?-D-GlcNAc-(1->?)- group; the remaining R1 and R2 atoms are hydrogens.

A polysaccharide that is alpha-D-Manp-(1->3)-[beta-D-Manp-(1->6)]-beta-D-Manp-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcpNAc-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcpNAc in which one hydroxy group in each of the terminal mannose moieties has been converted into the corresponding Neu5Gc-(1->?)-?-D-Gal-(1->?)-?-D-GlcNAc-(1->?)- glycoside. For the structure shown, one of the R1 atoms and one of the R2 atoms represents a Neu5Gc-(1->?)-?-D-Gal-(1->?)-?-D-GlcNAc-(1->?)- group; the remaining R1 and R2 atoms are hydrogens.

A polysaccharide that is GlyTouCan G22140GZ in which the 2-acetamido-beta-D-glucopyranosyl group bearing the anomeric hydroxy group has been glycosylated at position 6 by an alpha-L-fucosyl group. For the structure shown, one of the R1 atoms and one of the R2 atoms represents a ?-D-Gal-(1->?)-?-D-GlcNAc-(1->?)- group; the remaining R1 and R2 atoms are hydrogens.

A member of the class of acrylamides that is acrylamide which is substituted at positions 2 and 3 by 2-furyl and 5-nitro-2-furyl groups, respectively (the trans isomer). Formerly used as a food preservative, it was withdrawn from the market following suspicions of carcenogenicity.
